{"search_data": "DelhiDelhi Govt. Approves 7 New Destinations in Mukhyamantri Tirth Yatra Yojna Delhi govt. cabinet has approved 7 new destinations including Rameshwaram, Puri, Tirupati, Shirdi under Mukhyamantri Tirth Yatra Yojana 2019 \u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u0922\u093c\u0947\u09027 New Destinations in Mukhyamantri Tirth Yatra YojanaNow the proposal of dept. of Revenue of addition of seven new routes has been given clearance and approval in the cabinet committee meeting of Delhi government. These approved 7 routes would be added to already existing and functional 5 routes. The details of new destinations are as follows:-Delhi-Rameshwaram-Madurai-Delhi8 days ,Delhi Tirupati-Delhi7 daysDelhi Dwarkadhish-Nagesgwar-Delhi6 daysDelhi-JagannathPuri-Konark- Bhubaneshwar-Delhi7 daysDelhi-Shirdi-Shani Shinglapur-Delhi5 daysDelhi-Ujjain Onkareshwar-Delhi6 daysDelhi-BodhGaya-SarnathNot DecidedThe state govt. has also decided that in existing Ajmer Pushkar tour, Haldi Ghati destination may also be provided. The other functional routes are Delhi-Mathura-Vrindavan-Agra-Fatehpur Sikri, Delhi-Haridwar-Rishikesh-Neelkanth, Delhi-Amritsar-Wagah Border-Anandpur Sahib and Delhi-Vaishno Devi-Jammu.In addition to the 3 tier AC train, AC accomodation would also be provided wherever possible. Furthermore, wherever yatris are to transported through buses, govt. will make available 2*2 AC coaches for comfortable travel wherever possible.All the senior citizens who wants to be a part of the free pilgrimage scheme are issued certificates by the MLAs of their respective areas. Now the ministers of Delhi govt. and the chairman of the Tirth Yatra Vikas Samiti will also be able to issue certificates to the applicants.References\u2014 Mukhyamantri Teerth Yatra Yojana Package & Details \u2013 Read Here \u2014 Mukhyamantri Tirth Yatra Yojna Application / Registration \u2013 Read Here  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Reference Link: https://www.dailypioneer